ENTRY            D5211   20260120   20260508   20260508       D151
SUBENT        D5211001   20260120   20260508   20260508       D151
BIB                 14         31
TITLE      Analysis of the angular distribution for the elastic
           scattering of alpha particles from tritium at an
           energy of 84.2 MeV
AUTHOR     (S.Yu.Mezhevych,O.A.Ponkratenko,N.Keeley,Yu.S.Roznyuk,
           O.M.Povoroznyk,O.K.Gorpinich,V.I.Grantsev,
           O.O.Jachmenjov,K.K.Kisurin,S.E.Omelchuk,B.A.Rudenko,
           L.I.Slyusarenko,B.G.Struzhko,I.I.Vertegel)
INSTITUTE  (4UKRIJD,3POLIPJ)
FACILITY   (ISOCY,4UKRIJD) U-240 isochronous cyclotron
EXP-YEAR   (2014)
REFERENCE  (J,EPJ/A,61,204,2025)
           #doi:10.1140/epja/s10050-025-01683-6
SAMPLE     The target was manufactured using a titanium backing
            (5.39 mg/cm2 thick) saturated with tritium
            (equivalent to a thickness of 0.29 mg/cm2).
DETECTOR   (TELES,SIBAR,NAICR) Three deltaE-E telescopes placed
           on movable platforms. The deltaE stages consisted of
           150 mu-m thick silicon surface barrier detectors,
           with 2.5 mm thick NaI(Tl) detectors forming the E
           stages.
METHOD     (EXTB,EDE)
CORRECTION Corrected for background.
ADD-RES    (POT,COMP) Spectroscopic amplitudes, parameters of
           the nucleus-nucleus potentials were determined.
           Optical model and the coupled-reaction-channels
           method were used.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) Errors include both the statistical errors
           and uncertainties from the spectrum fitting procedure.
STATUS     (APRVD) Entry proofread by S.Yu.Mezhevych
HISTORY    (20260120C) UkrNDC
           (20260119R) Data received from S.Yu.Mezhevych
ENDBIB              31
